2
00:01:39.016 --> 00:01:40.684
Do you know who this belongs to?

3
00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:45.063
Do you?

4
00:01:50.193 --> 00:01:51.028
Answer me!

5
00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:54.031
It's mine.

6
00:01:58.785 --> 00:02:02.998
I don't think Gerson would agree.
Do you know Gerson?

7
00:02:07.419 --> 00:02:08.712
I don't think she's met Gerson.

8
00:02:10.631 --> 00:02:12.507
Do you know what we do...

9
00:02:13.425 --> 00:02:15.135
to people who try to steal from Gerson?

10
00:02:18.388 --> 00:02:19.264
On the ground!

11
00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:20.223
Let's go.

12
00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:23.101
Fuck.

13
00:02:24.061 --> 00:02:26.813
-Let go!
-Oh. being so brave. Go on.

14
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:30.275
I know what we're gonna do with you.

15
00:02:32.069 --> 00:02:32.903
Let her go.

16
00:02:35.072 --> 00:02:37.407
Next time you'll know better. bitch.

17
00:02:40.369 --> 00:02:41.328
Let's go!

18
00:02:59.638 --> 00:03:03.600
A NETFLIX ORIGINAL SERIES

19
00:03:58.613 --> 00:04:01.616
CHAPTER 03
CORRIDOR

20
00:04:07.622 --> 00:04:08.498
Nair?

21
00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:10.959
<i>Listen to me.</i>

22
00:04:11.042 --> 00:04:12.627
<i>You need to be careful.</i>

23
00:04:12.711 --> 00:04:15.172
<i>Aline was sent by Councilor Matheus.</i>

24
00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:18.884
-So. they're coming after me.
-<i>They all share the same ideas.</i>

25
00:04:18.967 --> 00:04:21.845
<i>Increased transparency. an easier Process.</i>

26
00:04:21.928 --> 00:04:24.389
<i>If they find one shred of evidence</i>
<i>against you...</i>

27
00:04:25.307 --> 00:04:26.933
<i>my vote will count for nothing.</i>

28
00:04:27.017 --> 00:04:28.643
I have nothing to hide.

29
00:04:35.192 --> 00:04:37.235
I wonder how long
they're gonna make us wait.

30
00:04:37.319 --> 00:04:39.321
Until we die from anxiety.

31
00:04:45.118 --> 00:04:46.620
Oh. damn.

32
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:49.122
My bad. it's a close match.

33
00:04:49.206 --> 00:04:53.251
Yeah. We're doing our own test
to see who can get it in the pipe.

34
00:04:54.753 --> 00:04:57.297
Knock it off
before you get us all in trouble.

35
00:04:58.340 --> 00:04:59.674
Where's your competitive spirit?

36
00:05:00.926 --> 00:05:02.803
-Let us try.
-It's our turn.

37
00:05:02.886 --> 00:05:04.221
Step behind the line.

38
00:05:04.304 --> 00:05:05.222
Watch out for the...

39
00:05:05.722 --> 00:05:06.890
-What?
-The chair.

40
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.477
-My turn.
-No.

41
00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:13.647
Here's the deal:
if Fernando gets it in on the first try.

42
00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.649
I'll give him my spot on the Offshore.

43
00:05:15.732 --> 00:05:18.235
-Then watch closely. douchebag.
-Go on.

44
00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:19.152
Watch.

45
00:05:20.362 --> 00:05:22.447
-Ow. fuck!
-Suck it!

46
00:05:23.073 --> 00:05:23.990
Nice!

47
00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:27.828
Idiot.

48
00:05:31.122 --> 00:05:32.958
Now you have to give me your spot.

49
00:05:36.795 --> 00:05:38.463
That's if you even pass.

50
00:05:39.047 --> 00:05:41.007
Think you're pretty tough. don't you?

51
00:05:42.634 --> 00:05:46.054
I have great aim.
but I'm not a great person.

52
00:05:46.137 --> 00:05:47.597
Watch yourself.

53
00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:25.385
Come in. Cássia.

54
00:06:27.429 --> 00:06:28.889
Oh. it's you.

55
00:06:29.973 --> 00:06:32.767
The next test just started.
May I watch it with you?

56
00:06:32.851 --> 00:06:34.603
-Of course.
-Thank you.

57
00:06:37.439 --> 00:06:38.273
Look.

58
00:06:39.107 --> 00:06:40.358
They were eliminated.

59
00:06:43.653 --> 00:06:45.739
Did you see she pissed herself?

60
00:06:45.822 --> 00:06:46.990
What happened?

61
00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:54.664
-Do you think they wash these clothes?
-That's what you're worried about?

62
00:07:06.801 --> 00:07:08.053
Hello. candidates.

63
00:07:08.678 --> 00:07:11.848
I hope you're happy
with the people in your group.

64
00:07:11.932 --> 00:07:16.186
After all. you did choose which candidate
to eliminate in the last test. right?

65
00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:17.145
More or less.

66
00:07:17.854 --> 00:07:19.731
-What's the test?
-It's simple.

67
00:07:20.315 --> 00:07:23.318
All you have to do
is cross the tunnel as a group.

68
00:07:24.361 --> 00:07:25.737
-Ready?
-Let's go.

69
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:30.992
Sorry. we just have to cross the tunnel?
That's all?

70
00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:33.578
What's inside? An alligator?

71
00:07:33.912 --> 00:07:34.746
Go.

72
00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:37.666
You have five minutes.

73
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.918
-How long is the tunnel?
-Good luck.

74
00:07:51.346 --> 00:07:53.139
Let's just move forward as a group.

75
00:08:01.523 --> 00:08:02.774
Come on. follow me.

76
00:08:14.577 --> 00:08:15.537
Guys...

77
00:08:16.913 --> 00:08:18.415
do you hear that hissing noise?

78
00:08:21.167 --> 00:08:22.794
Why did you kill Bruna?

79
00:08:23.962 --> 00:08:26.840
-What did you say?
-I didn't say anything. Michele.

80
00:08:31.177 --> 00:08:32.345
Guys. hold on.

81
00:08:32.429 --> 00:08:35.015
Less than a minute in
and the chicks are losing it.

82
00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:37.642
Guys. listen up.

83
00:08:38.309 --> 00:08:40.562
This is just a dark tunnel. That's all.

84
00:08:41.187 --> 00:08:42.814
Let's stick together.

85
00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:43.982
Sorry.

86
00:08:44.065 --> 00:08:45.942
If you touch me again. I'll turn you in.

87
00:08:46.735 --> 00:08:47.652
Fucking cheater.

88
00:08:50.238 --> 00:08:51.740
Slow and steady. guys.

89
00:08:52.907 --> 00:08:56.703
At this rate. we'll never make it across.
I'll go first. Excuse me.

90
00:09:18.725 --> 00:09:21.561
There's no "other side of the tunnel."
They're gonna kill us!

91
00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:29.069
What is this test about?
What's the concept?

92
00:09:29.152 --> 00:09:31.488
We release an odorless gas into the tunnel

93
00:09:31.571 --> 00:09:34.282
which has a profound effect
on the brain's occipital lobe.

94
00:09:34.365 --> 00:09:36.117
-Hence the hallucinations.
-Yes.

95
00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:38.453
In order to be worthy of joining us.

96
00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:41.998
they have to leave fear
and paranoia behind.

97
00:09:45.335 --> 00:09:46.669
We have to move faster.

98
00:09:46.753 --> 00:09:49.339
<i>-You're no good. Joana.</i>
<i>-You shouldn't have stolen from Gerson.</i>

99
00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:51.758
We need to get across
before something bad happens.

100
00:09:51.841 --> 00:09:54.511
-You're no good. Joana.
-How can you live with yourself?

101
00:09:54.594 --> 00:09:56.262
How can you sleep at night
after what you did?

102
00:09:56.346 --> 00:09:59.057
<i>If you go back.</i>
<i>Gerson will kill you. Joana.</i>

103
00:09:59.641 --> 00:10:02.811
<i>-His most precious thing.</i>
<i>-You're a murderer.</i>

104
00:10:02.894 --> 00:10:03.853
<i>Murderer.</i>

105
00:10:06.022 --> 00:10:08.983
<i>How can you sleep at night</i>
<i>knowing what you've done?</i>

106
00:10:09.067 --> 00:10:10.610
<i>You are a horrible person.</i>

107
00:10:10.693 --> 00:10:12.320
<i>It won't change what you did.</i>

108
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:14.989
Let me out of here!

109
00:10:15.865 --> 00:10:18.201
I crossed the tunnel! I need to get out!

110
00:10:19.244 --> 00:10:23.873
<i>This is a group test. candidate.</i>
<i>You only pass if the entire group passes.</i>

111
00:10:33.383 --> 00:10:36.302
<i>You're no good. Joana.</i>
<i>You are a horrible person.</i>

112
00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:39.055
<i>...will kill you.</i>

113
00:10:39.764 --> 00:10:41.474
<i>His most precious thing.</i>

114
00:10:43.059 --> 00:10:45.812
<i>Running away won't change anything.</i>
<i>You're a murderer!</i>

115
00:10:45.895 --> 00:10:48.064
<i>You are a horrible person.</i>

116
00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:54.112
-Joana. where were you?
-Negotiating your surrender. Rafael.

117
00:10:54.195 --> 00:10:55.613
-What?
-Come with me.

118
00:10:57.157 --> 00:10:58.283
That's a lie.

119
00:10:59.075 --> 00:11:00.618
There's a traitor in our group.

120
00:11:01.202 --> 00:11:03.663
There's a traitor in the group.
There's a traitor here.

121
00:11:03.746 --> 00:11:04.622
Hello. Michele.

122
00:11:05.874 --> 00:11:08.585
What's wrong?
Isn't this what you came for?

123
00:11:08.668 --> 00:11:10.879
To kill me? I deserve it.

124
00:11:12.422 --> 00:11:13.298
You killed him.

125
00:11:19.304 --> 00:11:21.764
<i>You're no good. Joana.</i>
<i>You're a horrible person.</i>

126
00:11:21.848 --> 00:11:23.057
It's some kind of gas!

127
00:11:23.141 --> 00:11:24.017
<i>Who are you?</i>

128
00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:27.854
What you're hearing or seeing.
it's the gas!

129
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:29.355
You're an embarrassment to your family.

130
00:11:29.439 --> 00:11:31.858
-We have to keep moving!
-I don't think he's an Álvares.

131
00:11:31.941 --> 00:11:34.068
-Shut up!
-You can argue at the other end.

132
00:11:34.152 --> 00:11:35.486
Let's go!

133
00:11:36.154 --> 00:11:37.113
Go!

134
00:11:44.662 --> 00:11:46.080
Come on. Ágata. let's go!

135
00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:51.878
She's gonna kill us. She's gonna kill us.

136
00:12:04.182 --> 00:12:05.350
Only one left.

137
00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:11.314
<i>Running away won't change</i>
<i>what you've done. You're a murderer!</i>

138
00:12:13.024 --> 00:12:14.525
-Come on!
-Keep your hands off me.

139
00:12:14.609 --> 00:12:16.778
-Come with me!
-Don't touch me!

140
00:12:16.861 --> 00:12:19.489
Do you know what we do
with traitors around here?

141
00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:20.823
I just did what I had to do!

142
00:12:20.907 --> 00:12:23.034
Rafael. you need to stop
breathing the gas.

143
00:12:28.331 --> 00:12:31.417
<i>-Murderer. You're a murderer!</i>
<i>-Murderer.</i>

144
00:12:31.501 --> 00:12:32.669
Shut up!

145
00:12:36.839 --> 00:12:40.927
Rafael... forget what you're seeing
and what you're hearing.

146
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:42.679
and come with me.

147
00:12:42.762 --> 00:12:44.681
Let's go! Trust me! Let's get out of here.

148
00:12:58.194 --> 00:12:59.570
Now. guys! Come on!

149
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:17.380
Congratulations.

150
00:13:17.964 --> 00:13:20.675
The effects of the hormones in the gas
will wear off soon.

151
00:13:20.758 --> 00:13:24.220
You will now be directed to the dorms.
This way. please.

152
00:13:30.601 --> 00:13:32.603
Ágata. it's over. Come with me.

153
00:13:42.572 --> 00:13:47.535
Cássia. I want you to find out everything
you can about this candidate. okay?

154
00:13:48.953 --> 00:13:51.039
I'm not sure about this test.

155
00:13:51.789 --> 00:13:55.835
I don't know if it's selecting
who we need for the Offshore.

156
00:13:58.337 --> 00:14:00.048
What about these plants. huh?

157
00:14:02.925 --> 00:14:04.802
Who picked these for you?

158
00:14:04.886 --> 00:14:06.512
Why couldn't I have picked them myself?

159
00:14:06.596 --> 00:14:08.014
Of course.

160
00:14:09.015 --> 00:14:12.143
Your office...
you have no pictures in here.

161
00:14:13.186 --> 00:14:15.313
No. I don't.

162
00:14:16.731 --> 00:14:19.484
Not even of Julia. your wife?

163
00:14:20.276 --> 00:14:21.152
No.

164
00:14:22.195 --> 00:14:23.946
Do you have any other comments?

165
00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:33.915
This is where you'll be sleeping.

166
00:14:43.257 --> 00:14:44.926
I can't believe I lost it in there.

167
00:14:45.593 --> 00:14:47.303
I swear it won't happen again.

168
00:14:48.304 --> 00:14:51.599
Lucky for us it was you and not Lucas.
Or we'd be gone.

169
00:14:51.682 --> 00:14:52.850
What about you?

170
00:14:52.934 --> 00:14:54.018
What did you see?

171
00:14:54.685 --> 00:14:55.645
Nothing.

172
00:14:56.145 --> 00:14:58.564
Right. You don't have to trust me.

173
00:14:59.148 --> 00:15:00.608
Just go it alone.

174
00:15:16.374 --> 00:15:18.418
They're making us sleep
in the engine room.

175
00:15:18.501 --> 00:15:20.753
Because where you slept before
was so much better.

176
00:15:27.593 --> 00:15:30.221
Ágata. relax. The test is over.

177
00:15:30.304 --> 00:15:31.848
-It's over.
-Here.

178
00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:33.599
She's been like this since the test.

179
00:15:39.772 --> 00:15:41.274
It's nothing to worry about.

180
00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:43.025
Give her time.

181
00:15:43.734 --> 00:15:45.445
The effects will wear off
after a good night's sleep.

182
00:15:45.528 --> 00:15:48.990
-No. I think she's having--
-We've done this test before.

183
00:15:49.073 --> 00:15:51.784
If she passed. she has to stay.

184
00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:54.328
But wait!
You're not going to do anything?

185
00:15:55.580 --> 00:15:58.082
Don't worry. He's an Offshore agent.

186
00:15:58.166 --> 00:16:01.252
-He knows what he's doing.
-I don't know.

187
00:16:01.335 --> 00:16:04.255
Maybe the gas is still wearing off.
but I feel kind of...

188
00:16:04.755 --> 00:16:06.090
I know. It was horrible.

189
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:08.509
Michele. what did you see?

190
00:16:09.302 --> 00:16:12.638
I thought I heard you say something
about your brother.

191
00:16:14.432 --> 00:16:20.938
Okay. I'm sorry.
I don't mean to pry or anything.

192
00:16:21.022 --> 00:16:22.231
I just want you to know--

193
00:16:30.364 --> 00:16:32.909
-I'm sorry.
-No.

194
00:16:56.140 --> 00:16:58.684
All eliminated candidates
have been escorted out.

195
00:16:58.768 --> 00:16:59.769
Okay.

196
00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:03.314
Except one who tried to sneak back
through the gate.

197
00:17:03.397 --> 00:17:05.107
Really? That's funny.

198
00:17:07.610 --> 00:17:10.112
Where was Aline going
with those questions?

199
00:17:10.196 --> 00:17:13.199
-She's just trying to throw me off.
-Know what I was thinking?

200
00:17:13.282 --> 00:17:17.912
Imagine if they put you. me. Aline.
and the Council members in the tunnel.

201
00:17:18.538 --> 00:17:19.789
Think we would pass?

202
00:17:19.872 --> 00:17:23.459
We're not here
to discuss hypotheses. okay?

203
00:17:24.043 --> 00:17:27.964
It's no wonder Aline is intrigued
by your personality. you know?

204
00:17:28.464 --> 00:17:30.550
Cássia. I have a Process to run.

205
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:35.304
I don't have time to joke around
or answer Aline's questions.

206
00:17:50.194 --> 00:17:53.489
Of course you passed.
Marco was leading your group.

207
00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:56.367
Who? Pretty boy over here?

208
00:17:56.826 --> 00:17:57.994
He totally lost it.

209
00:17:58.077 --> 00:18:00.454
You're telling me
Marco didn't lead you guys through?

210
00:18:03.541 --> 00:18:04.792
It was Joana.

211
00:18:04.875 --> 00:18:07.378
And he was the last one out.
Almost fucked everyone over.

212
00:18:07.461 --> 00:18:10.715
So what? Maybe it's because
I have a lot going on in my head.

213
00:18:10.798 --> 00:18:13.134
-It's called being profound.
-Right.

214
00:18:13.217 --> 00:18:14.093
Sorry.

215
00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:16.512
Do you think it'll be worth it?

216
00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:17.430
What?

217
00:18:17.513 --> 00:18:18.639
Passing.

218
00:18:19.640 --> 00:18:22.351
Of course.
Anything is better than this hellhole.

219
00:18:23.436 --> 00:18:25.396
Where do you want your kids
to grow up?

220
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:28.524
Inland? Or the Offshore?

221
00:18:28.608 --> 00:18:32.612
-You want to have kids?
-Sure I do. Why not?

222
00:18:32.695 --> 00:18:33.988
Those poor kids.

223
00:18:35.948 --> 00:18:39.201
No one really knows
what it's like over there.

224
00:18:39.285 --> 00:18:42.997
If there's a lot of green.
surrounded by nature.

225
00:18:43.080 --> 00:18:45.750
They're advanced. If they don't
need plants. they won't have them.

226
00:18:45.833 --> 00:18:49.795
The Offshore has a gigantic greenhouse.
They harvest everything they plant.

227
00:18:49.879 --> 00:18:55.301
When I was younger.
I pictured a place in the clouds.

228
00:18:56.302 --> 00:18:57.803
I know the greenhouse is for real.

229
00:18:57.887 --> 00:19:00.765
My grandma was a second cousin
to the Founding Couple.

230
00:19:00.848 --> 00:19:03.893
You know a lot of people
claim that. right?

231
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:06.520
She's the one who started building
the underground railroad!

232
00:19:06.604 --> 00:19:08.439
Sure. the tunnel... No.

233
00:19:09.774 --> 00:19:12.526
What do you mean?
It runs between the lake--

234
00:19:12.610 --> 00:19:14.612
Between the dried-up lake
and the landfill.

235
00:19:15.738 --> 00:19:16.614
Right.

236
00:19:16.697 --> 00:19:18.658
I know. It's run by militia.

237
00:19:19.825 --> 00:19:20.660
Oh. yeah?

238
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:24.580
Is that what you hallucinated about?

239
00:19:25.748 --> 00:19:28.751
No. I didn't see anything.

240
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:30.336
So. you're immune to the gas?

241
00:19:30.419 --> 00:19:34.715
Either that or you have nothing
in your head to hallucinate about.

242
00:19:35.257 --> 00:19:38.594
No fears. no regrets. no guilt?
Impossible.

243
00:19:48.562 --> 00:19:52.274
-What about that guy we killed yesterday?
-The one we beat to death.

244
00:19:52.358 --> 00:19:54.777
And now they wanna fuck up my house?

245
00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:57.196
The place where I raise my son?
Are they crazy?

246
00:19:57.279 --> 00:19:58.948
Let's go sort this shit out.

247
00:22:51.870 --> 00:22:52.913
I'm sorry.

248
00:22:53.706 --> 00:22:55.416
I didn't mean to...

249
00:23:03.173 --> 00:23:04.049
Die!

250
00:23:12.266 --> 00:23:13.267
Die!

251
00:23:15.477 --> 00:23:17.313
Stop. Ágata! Let her go!

252
00:23:17.396 --> 00:23:19.732
She's gonna kill us all! In the middle
of the night while we're sleeping!

253
00:23:19.815 --> 00:23:23.277
-She won't. Ágata. Trust me!
-She will!

254
00:23:23.360 --> 00:23:24.278
Everything is okay.

255
00:23:24.361 --> 00:23:25.571
-No!
-It's okay.

256
00:23:25.654 --> 00:23:27.948
Everything is fine. Trust me.

257
00:23:28.032 --> 00:23:30.618
Trust me. It's okay.

258
00:23:57.519 --> 00:23:59.605
Cássia. I'm already fixing the alarm.

259
00:23:59.688 --> 00:24:02.191
No. it went off by accident.

260
00:24:02.941 --> 00:24:04.526
I'll call you back.

261
00:24:09.657 --> 00:24:11.075
What are you doing here?

262
00:24:12.034 --> 00:24:14.453
I'm hungry.

263
00:24:17.039 --> 00:24:17.873
Come here.

264
00:24:36.141 --> 00:24:37.351
Wash your hands.

265
00:24:38.060 --> 00:24:39.687
Wash them like you mean it.

266
00:24:40.896 --> 00:24:41.980
That's it.

267
00:24:42.606 --> 00:24:43.816
Dry them quickly.

268
00:24:44.483 --> 00:24:45.442
Quick!

269
00:25:05.838 --> 00:25:07.005
Eat with your hands.

270
00:25:07.840 --> 00:25:09.258
I'm eating with my hands. too.

271
00:25:16.807 --> 00:25:18.976
Hey... Augusto.

272
00:25:21.729 --> 00:25:23.647
You were waiting for me. weren't you?

273
00:25:28.861 --> 00:25:32.031
I couldn't go see you
because things are difficult here.

274
00:25:32.865 --> 00:25:35.826
Someone has been watching me.
I'm being watched.

275
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:38.370
Do you understand?

276
00:25:41.957 --> 00:25:43.292
Listen to me.

277
00:25:48.088 --> 00:25:51.675
I might not be able to see you
as often as before.

278
00:25:53.510 --> 00:25:54.928
Things have changed around here.

279
00:25:57.931 --> 00:26:00.017
Answer me. Do you understand?

280
00:26:00.726 --> 00:26:02.060
I understand.

281
00:26:03.854 --> 00:26:05.272
Are you still hungry?

282
00:26:06.440 --> 00:26:07.316
Yes.

283
00:26:08.734 --> 00:26:10.110
Do you want my plate?

284
00:26:11.236 --> 00:26:12.237
Okay.

285
00:26:19.495 --> 00:26:21.038
I have a gift for you.

286
00:26:26.126 --> 00:26:27.169
Here.

287
00:27:18.345 --> 00:27:19.221
Here!

288
00:27:20.472 --> 00:27:22.808
Hey! What's going on?

289
00:27:22.891 --> 00:27:23.725
Help me.

290
00:27:23.809 --> 00:27:24.935
-What?
-I fucked up.

291
00:27:25.978 --> 00:27:26.979
You fucked up...

292
00:27:27.688 --> 00:27:29.356
What happened? Tell me.

293
00:27:30.482 --> 00:27:32.901
Do you still work with registrations?

294
00:27:33.944 --> 00:27:36.405
You were never registered?

295
00:27:39.366 --> 00:27:41.910
No. When there's no one
to take care of you.

296
00:27:41.994 --> 00:27:44.037
no one registers you either.

297
00:27:44.746 --> 00:27:45.873
Well...

298
00:27:46.915 --> 00:27:48.792
it can be done. but it's not...

299
00:27:50.085 --> 00:27:51.962
it's not that simple.

300
00:27:52.045 --> 00:27:56.508
I mean. it's not just.
"Take this. implant it. and done."

301
00:27:56.592 --> 00:27:58.177
They're going to kill me. Valéria.

302
00:27:59.469 --> 00:28:00.304
Or worse.

303
00:28:10.606 --> 00:28:12.649
Come. Come with me.

304
00:28:16.653 --> 00:28:17.487
Lie down.

305
00:28:18.322 --> 00:28:21.617
I'm gonna show you
how it all goes down.

306
00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:23.952
Look at this. This is a piece of liver.

307
00:28:24.036 --> 00:28:25.370
The registration is right here.

308
00:28:25.454 --> 00:28:30.334
The registration needs to stay in contact
with living cells. otherwise it turns off.

309
00:28:30.959 --> 00:28:32.044
Now...

310
00:28:33.629 --> 00:28:35.714
are you gonna tell me what's happening.

311
00:28:35.797 --> 00:28:37.799
or are you gonna keep me in the dark?

312
00:28:47.809 --> 00:28:49.478
NO RECORD

313
00:28:52.022 --> 00:28:53.315
Flip over on your side.

314
00:28:53.398 --> 00:28:56.318
It's going to be quick
and it won't hurt too much.

315
00:28:56.401 --> 00:28:57.236
Just a little.

316
00:28:57.986 --> 00:29:00.113
So many want
to go through the Process

317
00:29:00.197 --> 00:29:02.783
and you're trying to use it
so you can disappear.

318
00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:26.265
"Joana"?

319
00:29:26.348 --> 00:29:30.602
The name of the registration's owner.
The poor soul who died.

320
00:29:30.686 --> 00:29:34.815
No! You have to stay and rest
for at least a few hours.

321
00:29:35.274 --> 00:29:36.817
Thank you. Valéria.

322
00:29:47.035 --> 00:29:49.413
<i>-Gerson's son was killed.</i>
<i>-It was that girl.</i>

323
00:29:49.830 --> 00:29:51.415
<i>The lonely one.</i>

324
00:29:53.625 --> 00:29:55.585
<i>Know what we do to people</i>
<i>who steal from Gerson?</i>

325
00:29:55.669 --> 00:29:58.672
<i>There's a reward.</i>
<i>Do you know where she is?</i>

326
00:29:58.755 --> 00:30:01.591
<i>-Didn't you know her. Valéria?</i>
<i>-No. I don't know her.</i>

327
00:30:01.675 --> 00:30:03.677
<i>-You're a murderer.</i>
<i>-Murderer!</i>

328
00:30:09.891 --> 00:30:11.727
-How long was I--?
-Was it you?

329
00:30:13.020 --> 00:30:15.814
-What?
-Who killed his son.

330
00:30:19.151 --> 00:30:23.071
Gerson's already set a bounty
for the man who killed his son.

331
00:30:23.739 --> 00:30:24.865
Or woman.

332
00:30:24.948 --> 00:30:27.659
I didn't mean to get you involved.

333
00:30:27.743 --> 00:30:31.163
How could you do that? He was a child.

334
00:30:33.373 --> 00:30:35.542
I won't tell anyone that you helped me.

335
00:30:35.625 --> 00:30:37.753
I will know that I helped you! Get it?

336
00:30:41.214 --> 00:30:45.594
Now I know who you truly are.

337
00:30:46.345 --> 00:30:47.637
It was an accident.

338
00:30:48.138 --> 00:30:49.056
Get out.

339
00:30:51.725 --> 00:30:52.851
Get out of here!

340
00:30:53.560 --> 00:30:54.519
Right now!

341
00:31:29.721 --> 00:31:30.972
Ágata fell sleep.

342
00:31:31.848 --> 00:31:35.143
The gas took a toll on her. Poor thing.

343
00:31:36.395 --> 00:31:37.813
Are you feeling better?

344
00:31:42.275 --> 00:31:44.528
You don't have to talk to me.

345
00:31:44.986 --> 00:31:47.572
I just saved your life.
But what's a life. right?

346
00:31:48.782 --> 00:31:52.077
"Thanks. Rafael."
"No problem. Joana. You're welcome."

347
00:31:59.543 --> 00:32:02.254
I saw a kid. During the test.

348
00:32:03.463 --> 00:32:05.215
Then he was here in the corridor.

349
00:32:06.466 --> 00:32:08.969
Maybe the gas had a delayed effect on you.

350
00:32:11.096 --> 00:32:12.722
I know what I saw.

351
00:32:16.101 --> 00:32:17.352
I know what I did.

352
00:32:37.539 --> 00:32:39.624
You're not a bad person. Joana.

353
00:32:39.708 --> 00:32:41.710
What do you think you know about me?

354
00:32:41.793 --> 00:32:44.379
I don't really know... anything.

355
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:47.048
But I feel it.

356
00:32:48.675 --> 00:32:50.093
You saved me in that test.

357
00:32:52.721 --> 00:32:57.601
I think that you blackmailed
your way into an alliance.

358
00:32:58.101 --> 00:33:01.897
But after today. I think we could...
extend that alliance.

359
00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:03.148
What do you think?

360
00:33:05.192 --> 00:33:07.986
Joana. I know you won't turn me in.

361
00:33:08.820 --> 00:33:13.200
Especially since I can turn you in. too.

362
00:33:18.747 --> 00:33:19.623
Joana...

363
00:33:20.749 --> 00:33:25.212
we may have gotten where we are
doing things the wrong way...

364
00:33:27.547 --> 00:33:29.466
but I believe we're doing
the right thing now.

365
00:33:30.884 --> 00:33:32.177
In our own way.

366
00:33:33.929 --> 00:33:38.558
I don't know what you did
or what you saw in the tunnel.

367
00:33:38.642 --> 00:33:40.185
I don't give a fuck.

368
00:33:41.102 --> 00:33:42.062
I don't wanna know.

369
00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:47.317
I know. I feel...

370
00:33:47.943 --> 00:33:49.444
that you're a good person.

371
00:33:52.614 --> 00:33:54.199
You're the only one who doubts that.

372
00:34:05.085 --> 00:34:06.086
Here.

373
00:34:20.225 --> 00:34:21.101
Ezequiel?

374
00:34:25.605 --> 00:34:27.399
Stay here. Be quiet.

375
00:34:32.279 --> 00:34:34.114
I saw your light was on. May I come in?

376
00:34:35.448 --> 00:34:36.283
Of course.

377
00:34:38.660 --> 00:34:40.662
I didn't realize you were having dinner.

378
00:34:41.913 --> 00:34:44.332
Yes. once in a while I get hungry.

379
00:34:47.043 --> 00:34:48.044
Did you have company?

380
00:34:50.088 --> 00:34:53.091
Is that your final question
or are you just getting started?

381
00:34:55.594 --> 00:34:56.428
Aline...

382
00:34:57.387 --> 00:35:00.682
-let's put an end to this.
-There's no interrogation.

383
00:35:01.683 --> 00:35:05.145
I know very well why you are here

384
00:35:05.228 --> 00:35:06.980
and who sent you.

385
00:35:09.149 --> 00:35:09.983
The Council.

386
00:35:10.066 --> 00:35:11.651
Oh. the Council.

387
00:35:12.277 --> 00:35:13.486
I know exactly...

388
00:35:14.487 --> 00:35:16.114
who from the Council sent you.

389
00:35:17.032 --> 00:35:17.991
And why.

390
00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:22.912
The good thing about our society.
the beauty of it...

391
00:35:23.413 --> 00:35:25.582
is that each one of us made it
through the Process.

392
00:35:26.082 --> 00:35:28.960
You simply check anyone's ID
and their registration

393
00:35:29.044 --> 00:35:31.004
to find out exactly who they are.

394
00:35:31.087 --> 00:35:35.133
And there's no room for lies.
Or secrets.

395
00:35:38.928 --> 00:35:41.556
-But for now. I'll let you relax.
-Thank you.

396
00:35:44.309 --> 00:35:46.102
And. please. just one last question.

397
00:35:46.186 --> 00:35:50.273
Is it common for anyone to leave
the building during the Process?

398
00:35:52.817 --> 00:35:54.611
No. That doesn't happen.

399
00:35:55.570 --> 00:35:56.488
Okay.

400
00:36:01.201 --> 00:36:02.285
Good night. Ezequiel.

401
00:36:10.043 --> 00:36:12.128
I have to get you out of here right now.

402
00:36:16.716 --> 00:36:17.550
Where is it?

403
00:36:27.602 --> 00:36:28.436
Listen...

404
00:36:29.270 --> 00:36:31.189
I meant what I said. okay?

405
00:36:31.272 --> 00:36:32.982
You can never come here again.

406
00:36:34.442 --> 00:36:35.276
Never.

407
00:36:41.199 --> 00:36:42.033
Go.

408
00:37:04.347 --> 00:37:05.598
You should be sleeping.

409
00:37:06.391 --> 00:37:07.517
I can't.

410
00:37:09.477 --> 00:37:10.645
Are you worried?

411
00:37:11.438 --> 00:37:12.689
Thinking about stupid stuff.

412
00:37:14.441 --> 00:37:15.567
Not that.

413
00:37:15.650 --> 00:37:18.111
For a minute.
I could see myself on the Offshore.

414
00:37:18.194 --> 00:37:19.279
That's not stupid.

415
00:37:20.196 --> 00:37:21.948
And you were there with me.

416
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:34.043
We're here to pass the Process.

417
00:37:35.587 --> 00:37:38.381
-We can't get distracted.
-Yes. of course.

418
00:37:40.967 --> 00:37:44.095
-Do you understand?
-Yes. I was gonna say the same thing.

419
00:37:50.894 --> 00:37:52.103
Not that I didn't like it.

420
00:37:53.563 --> 00:37:58.485
It was probably just the gas talking.
It probably made us a little high.

421
00:37:58.568 --> 00:38:00.612
Totally. It was probably the gas.

422
00:38:03.156 --> 00:38:04.199
Probably.

423
00:38:05.116 --> 00:38:07.494
-Good night.
-Good night.

424
00:38:40.401 --> 00:38:41.236
What's up?

425
00:38:43.530 --> 00:38:44.405
Thank you.

426
00:40:06.279 --> 00:40:07.113
What's up. Joana?

427
00:40:07.906 --> 00:40:09.949
How long has it been? Is it daytime yet?

428
00:40:10.033 --> 00:40:12.869
-This wall wasn't here before.
-Are you sure?

429
00:40:13.411 --> 00:40:15.914
Yes. We came in through here yesterday.

430
00:40:26.299 --> 00:40:27.258
Wake up!

431
00:40:27.342 --> 00:40:28.468
Everyone. wake up!

432
00:40:28.885 --> 00:40:31.763
Listen. they blocked the exit.
We're trapped in here.

433
00:40:58.206 --> 00:40:59.165
Hey!

434
00:41:00.333 --> 00:41:01.584
Is anybody out there?

435
00:42:15.908 --> 00:42:17.910
Subtitle translation by João Neto

435
00:42:18.305 --> 00:43:18.545
